      • buildTermContextMatrix

        public float[][] buildTermContextMatrix​(java.lang.String trainingCorpus,
                                        int dim,
                                        java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,​java.lang.Integer> hashMap)
                                 throws java.io.IOException,
                                        java.io.FileNotFoundException
        Function to build the Term-Context Matrix by accepting the word2.txt file. v (lowercase) = all words in a document V (capital) = all unique words in the lexicon
        Parameters:
        trainingCorpus - word2.txt file path
        dim - The dimensions of the matrix, which is |V| by |V| or the size of the lexicon.
        hashMap - All of the unique words in the lexicon. Time Complexity: O(v * V^3 * V^2) Space Complexity: O(V^6)
        Returns:
        The term-context matrix after calculating PPMI and its adjustments
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - Handles any IO issues that may occur.
        java.io.FileNotFoundException - Throws when file is not found in directory.

      • ppmi

        public float ppmi​(float[][] matrix,
                  int indexWord1,
                  int indexWord2,
                  float matrixTotal,
                  float rowTotal,
                  float colTotal)
        Function to be used for calculating the PPMI (Positive Pointwise Mutual Information) in order to translate raw frequencies into normalized data. V = all unique terms in lexicon.
        Parameters:
        matrix - Term-context matrix.
        indexWord1 - Index position of the row.
        indexWord2 - Index position of the column.
        matrixTotal - The total of the entire termContextMatrix in raw frequencies.
        rowTotal - The total of the current row.
        colTotal - The total of the current column. Time Complexity: O(1) Space Complexity: O(V^2)
        Returns:
        PPMI value for that entry in the term-context matrix.

      • ppmiAdjustment

        public float ppmiAdjustment​(float word,
                            float power,
                            float sum)
        PPMI Adjustment for the rare cases of words that causes extremely high PPMI values
        Parameters:
        word - The sum of that row's values.
        power - The power to raise the row's values by.
        sum - Total sum of matrix. Time Complexity: O(1) Space Complexity: O(1)
        Returns:
        The adjusted PPMI value.
